{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":159774,"duration_api_ms":158471,"num_turns":48,"result":"The fix has been implemented. Here's a summary of the changes:\n\n## Changes Made\n\n### 1. `dvc/repo/reproduce.py`\n- Added import for `RunCacheNotSupported` from `dvc.stage.cache`\n- Wrapped the `self.stage_cache.pull(None)` call in a try/except block to catch `RunCacheNotSupported` exception and continue\n\n### 2. `dvc/repo/fetch.py`\n- Added import for `RunCacheNotSupported` from `dvc.stage.cache`\n- Modified exception handling to also catch `RunCacheNotSupported` (in addition to `DownloadError`)\n\n## Rationale\n\nThe release note mentions \"repro: Continue on RunCacheNotSupported\" (PR #9511). The `RunCacheNotSupported` exception is raised in `dvc/stage/cache.py::transfer()` when the remote filesystem doesn't support run cache (e.g., HTTP remotes).\n\nThe fix ensures that when `dvc.reproduce(pull=True)` or `dvc fetch --run-cache` is called with a remote that doesn't support run cache:\n1. The exception is caught\n2. The operation continues gracefully instead of crashing\n\nThis is a minimal, focused fix that addresses the specific issue described in the release notes.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"dc90b787-a6fc-49a4-9887-b0371630de3c","total_cost_usd":1.7014449000000003,"usage":{"input_tokens":504875,"cache_creation_input_tokens":554,"cache_read_input_tokens":144120,"output_tokens":7577,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"cache_deleted_input_tokens":0,"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"MiniMax-M2.5-highspeed":{"inputTokens":512108,"outputTokens":7907,"cacheReadInputTokens":148128,"cacheCreationInputTokens":554,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":1.7014449000000003,"contextWindow":196000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uu